3. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper's focus on sequential decision making and planning policies is highly relevant to robotics, where robots need to make decisions and plan actions in real-time. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper's use of MPC-inspired policies and focus on control and planning make it relevant to the systems and control community. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision): Although not the main focus of the paper, the use of neural networks and planning policies could have applications in computer vision tasks such as object tracking and recognition.
